1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 6=

3
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:41,189
I'll help you get
your granddaughter's child support.

4
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:41,589
Good, good.

5
00:01:41,590 --> 00:01:43,960
- Can you start giving out the eggs now?
- Right.

6
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:44,999
Alright.

7
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,359
No rush.

8
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,589
Cook some noodles

9
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:49,029
and crack an egg in

10
00:01:49,030 --> 00:01:51,309
It'll be perfect poached. Here.

11
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:53,879
Wait, so all that talking

12
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,400
is only worth one egg?

13
00:01:57,670 --> 00:01:58,999
There are four of us.

14
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,749
We need one for every bowl.

15
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:02,270
Right, right.

16
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:03,359
Don't push!

17
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,669
Stop pushing! Everyone, back off!

18
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:07,430
Calm down!

19
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:11,640
Hello?

20
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,390
Who is this?

21
00:02:13,790 --> 00:02:14,719
Mr. Zhou?

22
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:15,839
I'm in the middle of something.

23
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,830
I have to go. Goodbye.

24
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:21,320
Stop grabbing!

25
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:25,839
Stop it!

26
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,110
Mr. Yao.

27
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,159
I'm here! Brother.

28
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,880
Dad, I'm coming.

29
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,560
Judge Shen.

30
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,559
My dad missed me.

31
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,309
- Brother!
- Dad!

32
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:36,469
I've come to see you.

33
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:38,909
Did you miss me, Dad?

34
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:40,069
I brought you some grapes.

35
00:02:40,070 --> 00:02:41,439
Let me massage your legs, Brother.

36
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,679
Here, Dad. Your favorite.

37
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,999
He can't eat those.

38
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,839
You'll choke him to death!

39
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,309
Don't worry, Dad. I'll peel them.

40
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:50,029
I'm even taking the seeds out.

41
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:50,999
Don't squeeze him!

42
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,719
What's wrong?

43
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,029
He's in pain all over.

44
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,469
He's my brother. I'd know that.

45
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:56,159
He can't take it.

46
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,119
You're so difficult.

47
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,880
Alright, Brother.
Let me empty your urinal.

48
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,309
Look.

49
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,309
The judge came to see you himself.

50
00:03:04,310 --> 00:03:05,399
Tell them.

51
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,110
Who am I to you?

52
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:09,559
The caretaker.

53
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,200
Don't get ahead of yourself.

54
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,589
You're just the help.

55
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:13,839
Stay out of this, okay?

56
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,909
I'm his partner.

57
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,349
What partner?

58
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:17,909
Who can prove that?

59
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:18,839
Where's your license?

60
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,559
We didn't have time to get one.

61
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,439
Why didn't he marry you when he could?

62
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:24,189
You've got a lot of nerve.

63
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:25,469
Where were you the past forty years?

64
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:26,399
None of your business.

65
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,679
Where were you
when he had a fever?

66
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:29,719
Now you show up with these grapes?

67
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,159
Show some respect!

68
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,600
What's that supposed to mean?

69
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,999
Drop this "loving daughter" act.

70
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,950
Enough, both of you.

71
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,040
Judge Shen, she hit me!

72
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,830
Dad, look! She hit me!

73
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,719
Go play with your grapes.

74
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,789
Judge Shen, look how much he's peeing.

75
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,160
He's doing great.

76
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,950
He'll definitely live to a hundred.

77
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,110
Oh, so even his pee is "good" now?

78
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,719
Why don't you drink it while it's warm?

79
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,110
Get lost!

80
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,309
Here, Dad.

81
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:02,839
Try some of these.

82
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,439
Open up.

83
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,439
Come on.

84
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,349
I'm going to give your chest a wipe.

85
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:08,720
Don't touch him!

86
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:09,589
Stop that.

87
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:10,839
You'll break something.

88
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,559
I'll put it back

89
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,789
when I'm done.

90
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:15,879
Put what back? Do you even know how?

91
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,999
Stop moving him.

92
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,439
You're not a doctor. What do you know?

93
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,270
I'm the one who's been doing it!

94
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,439
Everyone, please.

95
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,709
Could you step out for a moment?

96
00:04:24,710 --> 00:04:25,749
I need a word with Mr. Yao.

97
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:26,999
Judge Shen, here.

98
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,949
Try this. It's delicious.

99
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:31,269
- Here, spit the seeds out here.
- Thank you. I'll get him some water.

100
00:04:31,270 --> 00:04:32,119
Why is he coughing?

101
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:32,829
Is he choking?

102
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:34,069
Rub your ears, quick!

103
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,320
It's okay.

104
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:38,200
Brother!

105
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,510
Out! Everyone out!

106
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,149
What happened?

107
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:42,440
You're going to kill him!

108
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:43,309
Leave!

109
00:04:43,310 --> 00:04:44,760
Dad, what's wrong?

110
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:45,949
Doctor, please save my father!

111
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:46,799
Get out, now!

112
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,920
I'm telling you, this is on you.

113
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,710
Don't just feed him anything!

114
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,800
Miss?

115
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,070
Excuse me, miss?

116
00:05:04,150 --> 00:05:05,440
Are you calling me?

117
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,239
Miss.

118
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:09,039
Isn't the "legal advice for eggs" session

119
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,709
under the bridge?

120
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,309
Today's community outreach program

121
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:13,359
is actually over.

122
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,749
Check back another day.

123
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,070
Wait, miss.

124
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,269
I need but a moment.

125
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:18,559
I was wondering,

126
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,920
who can help me write a legal complaint?

127
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:22,309
A complaint?

128
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,830
I can do that for you.

129
00:05:24,150 --> 00:05:24,949
And your name?

130
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,270
My surname is Liu.

131
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,559
Ms. Liu.

132
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,320
How can I help you?

133
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:32,240
My husband just passed away,

134
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,360
and I can't get in touch
with the children.

135
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,440
Looking to divide the asset?

136
00:05:38,710 --> 00:05:40,509
If anything happens to my brother,

137
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:41,999
you're all murderers.

138
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,320
I'll make you pay!

139
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,069
Good grief, who do you think you are?

140
00:05:45,070 --> 00:05:45,709
What do you mean?

141
00:05:45,710 --> 00:05:46,679
I'm his brother!

142
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,070
Where were you before this?

143
00:05:48,310 --> 00:05:48,919
Judge!

144
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,950
Don't listen to their nonsense.

145
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,149
I'm his biological daughter.

146
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:53,949
His only daughter.

147
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:55,360
Ignore her!

148
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,599
Let's go inside.

149
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,189
We'll hear it from the old man himself.

150
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:01,119
I'm his brother.

151
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,709
I'm telling you the truth!

152
00:06:02,710 --> 00:06:04,189
I'm his spouse!

153
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:05,799
And where were you two days ago?

154
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,320
Sorry, excuse me. I have to take this.

155
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:11,440
I can't hear you.

156
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,590
What?

157
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,439
Go ahead.

158
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,269
The reception is terrible.
I'm heading out.

159
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:17,510
I'll talk outside.

160
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:17,919
Wait!

161
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,879
- Don't go!
- Keep talking, I'm listening!

162
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:19,919
Do you see this?

163
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,189
This is what my family is like.

164
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:22,709
- I'm not good with words...
- We must sign it now!

165
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:24,829
We'll talk to the judge in a bit.
Let's find the judge!

166
00:06:24,830 --> 00:06:27,200
Listen to me! Just listen!

167
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,309
Listen!

168
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,599
It's not up to me!

169
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,949
Wait for me!

170
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:32,200
- Slow down!
- Officer!

171
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,030
Hold on, I'll be right back!

172
00:06:47,270 --> 00:06:48,560
Judge Shen!

173
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,070
You...

174
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,709
You sure bolted out of there.

175
00:06:51,710 --> 00:06:53,709
Well, I did have a call.

176
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:55,879
Plus, it gives the family
a chance to cool off.

177
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,269
Unbelievable.

178
00:06:57,270 --> 00:06:58,510
You sound experienced.

179
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,879
Don't worry, take it slow.

180
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:01,799
You'll learn how to handle this in time.

181
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,030
Let's go.

182
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,440
You got it.

183
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,760
(A man is on his deathbed.)

184
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:12,309
(All his longing and loneliness)

185
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:14,389
(met only by the chaotic theater)

186
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,950
(of his bickering relatives.)

187
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:19,679
(In this messy reality we call life,)

188
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:22,679
(family ties become bargaining chips.)

189
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,030
(It's merely an extension
of human greed.)

190
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:29,240
(The law might not be able
to judge a lack of love,)

191
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:31,120
(but in a fight like this,)

192
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,390
(does anyone truly win?)

193
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:38,359
Don't worry, Ms. Liu.

194
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:40,440
You're completely in the right here.

195
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:41,559
Since you and your husband

196
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,189
were officially married for so long,

197
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:45,150
they can't ignore
their obligations to you.

198
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,389
The truth is,

199
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:48,440
I didn't actually want to sue them.

200
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,760
But they've gone completely missing.

201
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,390
People told me

202
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,880
this was my only option.

203
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:57,390
I see.

204
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,389
Well,

205
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:00,070
(Jindian Law Firm)
we're here.

206
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:01,599
Why don't you come in for a bit?

207
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,239
That's alright.
I don't want to be a bother.

208
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,630
I'll wait for your letter.

209
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:07,000
Rest assured, I'll handle it.

210
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,360
Take care.

211
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:24,709
Hello?

212
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:25,829
Mr. Zhou.

213
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:27,150
Where are you?

214
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:28,999
I'm in the neighborhood,

215
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,069
doing the legal outreach program.

216
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:31,999
It's packed here.

217
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,319
Absolute chaos.

218
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,599
I don't have time for this.
Find another lawyer.

219
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,269
I'm hanging up.

220
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:37,359
I'm looking right at you.

221
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,710
Looking at me?

222
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:48,870
What a coincidence.

223
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,029
They say

224
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:57,789
a comfortable retirement

225
00:08:57,790 --> 00:08:59,269
requires financial independence

226
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,870
and the capacity for self-care.

227
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:03,590
Otherwise, you're at the mercy
of your children's conscience.

228
00:09:03,790 --> 00:09:05,990
At least Mr. Yao has
the money part down.

229
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:10,879
People say being old and broke
is a nightmare,

230
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:13,350
but being old and rich
might actually be worse.

231
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,269
It's self-care that really matters.

232
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,719
If this were just about child support,

233
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,230
it would be a simple fix.

234
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,470
But the man is sitting on a goldmine,

235
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,599
yet he's stuck with these vultures.

236
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,599
You think
they actually want to help him?

237
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,590
They're just circling for his money.

238
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,269
How about this?

239
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:30,200
Leave his care
to a professional nurse

240
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,999
and keep those clowns out of it.

241
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,669
Set up regular visiting hours

242
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:35,079
so they can perform their "devotion"

243
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:37,029
and feel important
in front of the old man.

244
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:38,509
For big decisions, they vote.

245
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:39,479
Collective action.

246
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,749
Joint oversight of the books.

247
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,230
If it's about money,
let's put it all on the table.

248
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,599
They'll keep each other in check,
and can drop the act.

249
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,920
The money isn't the root issue here.

250
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:49,789
It's proximity.

251
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:51,920
Whoever is closest can isolate him

252
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,269
and manipulate his decisions

253
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:55,440
on how the estate is divided.

254
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,199
He should control his assets

255
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,800
while he's alive.

256
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,079
As for the inheritance,

257
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,599
have him draft a will

258
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,879
and put it in a registry.

259
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,599
Keep the details
from the children for now.

260
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,319
He can adjust it
based on their behavior

261
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,149
and reveal it only after he passes.

262
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:09,269
It's the best way to maximize

263
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:10,839
their motivation to be good children.

264
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,079
It's the same logic

265
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,470
as hiding a secret imperial decree
behind a painting.

266
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,239
The best system is only as good
as the people running it.

267
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,320
The old man is too sick for this.

268
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,230
The more enthusiastic those kids get,

269
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:26,320
for him, the more it's actually going to hurt.

270
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:35,360
(Mom)

271
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:37,359
Mom?

272
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,549
What do you want for dinner?

273
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:39,839
I'm going grocery shopping.

274
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,269
I'm not coming back tonight.

275
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:43,509
You're seriously skipping
the one night a week

276
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:45,479
you're supposed to act

277
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,230
like a son and grandson?

278
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,110
Besides, your grandpa is back.

279
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,029
The least you could do
is show your face.

280
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:53,239
Look,

281
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,680
that's completely different.

282
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,990
Are you trying to be a bad son?

283
00:10:57,030 --> 00:10:58,549
I'm out on a field investigation.

284
00:10:58,550 --> 00:11:00,350
I'll probably have to work late tonight.

285
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,830
Is that so?

286
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,800
Fine, I'll check back with you later.

287
00:11:04,630 --> 00:11:05,750
Bye.

288
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,950
No overtime today, right?

289
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,590
You can head home.

290
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,230
Not bad.

291
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:16,750
It's a bit small, but quite cozy.

292
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,800
Have a seat.

293
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:22,280
What are these? The eggs you use
as bait for your clients?

294
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,680
If you like them,
take a couple home.

295
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,280
You can make some egg drop soup.

296
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:27,629
With these cheap things?

297
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:28,359
At a supermarket,

298
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,520
they'd be in the 50% off bin.

299
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:33,029
Honestly, the people coming
for these eggs

300
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:35,230
are just looking for a handout.

301
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,199
They're hardly the premium clients.

302
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,029
True.

303
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:38,789
If I were rich,

304
00:11:38,790 --> 00:11:40,479
I wouldn't be buying discount eggs.

305
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,070
I'd be handing out golden ones.

306
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,959
That'd be a bit too much.

307
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:46,320
But at least spring for free-range.

308
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,629
I heard about this one kind

309
00:11:47,630 --> 00:11:48,909
that you can eat raw.

310
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:50,389
You just crack it over a bowl of rice

311
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,640
and mix it right in.

312
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:53,669
One of those eggs

313
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:55,400
costs a small fortune.

314
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:56,599
If you used those,

315
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,629
you might actually attract
those high-end clients.

316
00:11:58,630 --> 00:11:59,509
Right.

317
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,149
If I ever get to work the CBD

318
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,959
or some fancy lakeside villa,

319
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,640
I'll be sure to try your little trick.

320
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,599
Offices in the CBD have their own

321
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,239
legal departments.

322
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,389
The villas are owned by the rich.

323
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:12,149
They have what you called...

324
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,429
Private attorneys.

325
00:12:13,430 --> 00:12:14,749
They wouldn't hire someone

326
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:15,719
from a rinky-dink firm

327
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,830
handing out cheap eggs.

328
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,509
Mr. Zhou,

329
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:21,549
it looks like you've had

330
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,359
enough of a break.

331
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,959
I need to head back to the neighborhood

332
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,999
to hand out more eggs.

333
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,389
Every little bit counts.

334
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:29,320
Seniors are my bread and butter.

335
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:31,400
What, are you kicking me out?

336
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,750
Look, I'm here for two reasons. First,

337
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,710
I forgot to give you
that gift from last time.

338
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,719
But more importantly,

339
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,750
I want to introduce you
to a premium client.

340
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,999
For real?

341
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,040
Dead serious.

342
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:47,470
My boss at the company.

343
00:12:47,510 --> 00:12:48,879
He's going through a divorce.

344
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,029
They haven't settled

345
00:12:50,030 --> 00:12:51,400
the assets yet.

346
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:53,160
Do you know how much we're talking?

347
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:54,920
Two hundred million.

348
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,149
Actually, it's 250 million.

349
00:12:57,150 --> 00:13:00,789
Doesn't your boss already
have his own lawyer?

350
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:02,590
He does.

351
00:13:03,670 --> 00:13:06,750
But his wife doesn't have one.

352
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,079
I think you're a good guy,

353
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,549
so I wanted to set you up.

354
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:13,950
And is the wife a housewife?

355
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,879
Is she the vulnerable party?

356
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,280
No income of her own?

357
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:18,239
No.

358
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,950
I can represent her with full authority.

359
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:21,950
Wait...

360
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,990
Suddenly you have "full authority"?

361
00:13:24,430 --> 00:13:26,470
Do you have someone on the inside?

362
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:27,550
No.

363
00:13:27,670 --> 00:13:29,830
For the last time, I don't know anyone.

364
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:32,079
I have zero connection to Judge Shen.

365
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:34,839
I rely purely on my expertise
and track record.

366
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:35,719
Expertise?

367
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,429
Anyone with a license
calls themselves an expert.

368
00:13:37,430 --> 00:13:38,079
And track record?

369
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,029
Good lawyers are hard to find,

370
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:42,149
but smooth-talking
con artists are everywhere.

371
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:42,959
Tell you the truth,

372
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,549
I don't trust lawyers.

373
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,359
I handled my own divorce,

374
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,280
and I didn't lose a single cent.

375
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:50,479
Your case was completely different.

376
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,609
The stakes aren't even comparable.

377
00:13:52,610 --> 00:13:53,669
Two hundred million.

378
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:54,319
Right?

379
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,509
I'm an award-winning lawyer.

380
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,909
Not to brag, but look.

381
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:59,389
(Qin Rui)
"Awarded to Qin Rui for Excellence."

382
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:01,800
Every lawyer
has their own "little tricks."

383
00:14:02,790 --> 00:14:03,999
I'd like to hear about yours.

384
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,800
What are your special tricks?

385
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:07,149
Are you free tomorrow?

386
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:10,029
If you are, let's go to
the Enforcement Department.

387
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:11,600
I'm meeting
my ex-wife for a settlement.

388
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,359
Wait...

389
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,040
That's a bit rushed.

390
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,520
You're really leaving this
until the last minute.

391
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,119
Well, we hit it off, didn't we?

392
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,509
First, your rates are fair.

393
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:21,269
Second, you've got "tricks" of yours.

394
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,029
And third,

395
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:24,029
I still have to set you up
with the wife of my boss.

396
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,160
Right?

397
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,520
Fine.

398
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:33,070
It's a deal.

399
00:14:33,270 --> 00:14:34,400
Good.

400
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,199
You're back.

401
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,920
You're home early today.

402
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:47,149
Welcome home.

403
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,590
Peeling potatoes?

404
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,199
I was late. I didn't have time to shop.

405
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,079
So tonight,

406
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:54,269
it's potatoes and more potatoes.

407
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,549
Come on.

408
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:57,389
I'm taking you out for a real dinner.

409
00:14:57,390 --> 00:14:59,029
What? Where is this coming from?

410
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:00,119
Did you hit the jackpot?

411
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,269
I've got some cash now.

412
00:15:01,270 --> 00:15:02,509
Time to live it up.

413
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:04,479
Otherwise, I won't have the motivation

414
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,870
to earn it next time.

415
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,239
Look.

416
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,909
After Ms. Liu paid me,

417
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:11,669
I sent six thousand to my grandma.

418
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:13,269
That's six months of medical bills.

419
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:16,119
After the suit rental,
we've still got 2,600 yuan left.

420
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:18,800
How about we go to...

421
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,359
Granny's Place?

422
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,680
Granny's Place?

423
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,750
Isn't that the raw seafood spot?

424
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,479
You got food poisoning

425
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,429
at a buffet last time.

426
00:15:27,430 --> 00:15:28,479
You think you can handle

427
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,749
the raw stuff downstairs?

428
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:32,320
I just felt bad
that you've never tried it.

429
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:35,800
I wanted to treat you
to something different.

430
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:38,110
If I use my imagination,

431
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:39,599
it's basically the same

432
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,719
as that buffet anyway.

433
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:43,350
Look, I appreciate the thought,

434
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:46,160
but we can't afford
to splurge this month.

435
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:48,239
Why not?

436
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:51,280
Shen Xiezhi's bill is
coming any day now.

437
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:53,560
That's not going to stop us.

438
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,079
We have to live a little.

439
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,599
Things will work themselves out.

440
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,719
Come on. Let's go spend some money.

441
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,879
Give it a rest.

442
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:01,749
Forget it.

443
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,999
I'm serious.

444
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,119
Stop with the potatoes.

445
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,750
Let's go, move it!

446
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,999
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

447
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,909
If you'd handed this case
to me back then,

448
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,599
I never would've let you lose like that.

449
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,239
Toddlers usually

450
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,389
go to the mother.

451
00:16:21,390 --> 00:16:22,479
That's the general rule.

452
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,319
But in your case,

453
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,199
you definitely had a shot at winning.

454
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,160
The judge already ruled in her favor.

455
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:28,719
What's the point now?

456
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,599
Just hurry up

457
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,389
and get my visitation rights sorted.

458
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:32,749
We're heading
to the Enforcement Department

459
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:33,999
to meet their lawyer, right?

460
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,520
Yeah, so...

461
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:37,029
Before we go in,

462
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,119
could you put in a good word

463
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,640
with Judge Shen?

464
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:40,669
Wait!

465
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,470
There are people everywhere.

466
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,429
Keep it down!

467
00:16:43,430 --> 00:16:44,429
What you just said

468
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:45,830
could get us in deep trouble.

469
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,149
I've reviewed your case thoroughly.

470
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:50,199
You have no priors,
no history of domestic violence,

471
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,789
and no severe mental health issues.

472
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:52,909
There is zero evidence

473
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:55,479
that your visits would
harm the child's physical,

474
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,839
mental, or emotional development.

475
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:57,749
It's a simple matter

476
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:58,999
of talking to the other side

477
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,479
and picking a time and place.

478
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:02,719
Yeah, yeah, I get all that.

479
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,119
But my ex-wife is the problem.

480
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:06,270
I'm afraid she'll pull some stunt.

481
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:07,949
Since you and Judge Shen

482
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:08,949
are so tight,

483
00:17:08,950 --> 00:17:10,359
can't you just send a quick text?

484
00:17:10,360 --> 00:17:11,429
Put in a good word?

485
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:12,879
Not this again.

486
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,119
Stop looking for shortcuts.

487
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:14,759
Just go in there

488
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,149
and talk to her face-to-face.

489
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:17,790
Fine, fine. I trust you.

490
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:19,750
I'll be direct with them.

491
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:22,079
But you be direct with me too.

492
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:22,949
What's the story

493
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:24,440
with you and Judge Shen?

494
00:17:24,470 --> 00:17:25,669
Is there something

495
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,080
going on between you?

496
00:17:27,470 --> 00:17:28,669
Ms. Qin.

497
00:17:28,670 --> 00:17:29,990
Judge Shen.

498
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:33,120
I was just about to call you.

499
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:34,680
Me?

500
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:38,510
Do you have a moment?

501
00:17:39,990 --> 00:17:41,629
Sure, of course.

502
00:17:41,630 --> 00:17:43,750
You two talk.
I need to reply to a message.

503
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:45,790
Go ahead.

504
00:17:50,430 --> 00:17:51,600
So...

505
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:54,790
Judge Shen.

506
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:57,759
What can I do for you?

507
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:58,709
Wasn't that guy

508
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:01,470
at the Yunting Hotel that night?

509
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,200
Yes.

510
00:18:05,630 --> 00:18:06,389
Wait,

511
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:07,359
he's my client.

512
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,469
We have a meeting at 14:30
at the Enforcement Department.

513
00:18:09,470 --> 00:18:10,629
We were just heading over.

514
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:12,360
Who would've thought

515
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,629
I'd bump into you here?

516
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:14,790
I see.

517
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,640
A coincidence.

518
00:18:16,670 --> 00:18:17,429
It really is.

519
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:18,559
It's a simple case.

520
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,709
Just visitation rights.

521
00:18:19,710 --> 00:18:21,149
The job is purely procedural.

522
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:22,600
Right.

523
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:24,400
You don't have to explain.

524
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,669
Lawyers are free to come and go here.

525
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:29,120
Actually, I'm here about something else.

526
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:31,200
My side mirror.

527
00:18:35,950 --> 00:18:37,080
What?

528
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:39,310
Judge Shen...

529
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:41,790
What mirror?

530
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,990
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

531
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,710
I have a dashcam.

532
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:52,440
I've already seen the footage.

533
00:18:57,910 --> 00:18:59,429
Judge Shen, I am so sorry.

534
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:00,990
I didn't do it on purpose.

535
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,319
It was...

536
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,709
It was a total...

537
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,160
A total accident.

538
00:19:07,710 --> 00:19:09,440
Whether you call it

539
00:19:09,710 --> 00:19:11,080
a coincidence,

540
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,469
an accident,

541
00:19:12,470 --> 00:19:15,279
or a deliberate sabotage,

542
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,909
the repair bill is the same regardless.

543
00:19:17,910 --> 00:19:19,759
I've checked with the dealer.

544
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,839
Parts and labor come to a total

545
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:23,279
of 3,386 yuan.

546
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:24,360
What...

547
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,510
Over three thousand yuan?

548
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:30,599
Have you considered another shop?

549
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,669
I bought the car there.

550
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:34,799
They've done every service
and repair since.

551
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,149
That's the standard market price.

552
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:37,389
I have the invoice.

553
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:39,440
If you want to dispute the cost,

554
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:40,990
we can call the traffic police.

555
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:43,230
No. No dispute.

556
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,429
Fine.

557
00:19:44,430 --> 00:19:45,839
How would you like to pay?

558
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,080
WeChat is fine.

559
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:53,550
I'll have the receipt sent to your firm.

560
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,480
(Wallet Balance: 436 yuan)

561
00:19:58,950 --> 00:20:01,200
Or would you prefer to see it
before you pay?

562
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,519
Of course not.

563
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,790
It's not like the court
is going anywhere.

564
00:20:05,950 --> 00:20:07,200
Judge Shen.

565
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:10,079
Could we do installments?

566
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,200
Installments?

567
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:13,949
How many?

568
00:20:13,950 --> 00:20:14,709
Well...

569
00:20:14,710 --> 00:20:16,669
Since it's 3,386 yuan,

570
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,039
I'll pay the 386 upfront today.

571
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:22,120
Then I'll split the remaining amount into

572
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,949
6 monthly payments of 500 yuan each.

573
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,230
Monthly payments.

574
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:30,840
If you want interest,

575
00:20:31,150 --> 00:20:32,710
I can...

576
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,119
Forget it.

577
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,920
Just pay the principal on time.

578
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:38,470
Your firm isn't skipping town, right?

579
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:39,990
Not a chance.

580
00:20:40,150 --> 00:20:41,429
With this prime location,

581
00:20:41,430 --> 00:20:42,790
we're not going anywhere.

582
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,640
Okay.

583
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:47,759
There you go.

584
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,039
Same time next month.

585
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,310
Judge Shen.

586
00:20:50,670 --> 00:20:51,599
Should we exchange contacts?

587
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,469
It'll make the monthly payments easier.

588
00:20:53,470 --> 00:20:54,600
No thanks.

589
00:20:59,670 --> 00:21:01,759
Just take a photo of my QR code.

590
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,710
You can just scan and pay from there.

591
00:21:10,710 --> 00:21:11,879
Right outside the courthouse?

592
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:12,949
You're actually paying him?

593
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:14,599
How much does he want?
Thirty thousand?

594
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:15,389
Three thousand.

595
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:16,079
That's a fair price.

596
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,599
I smashed his side mirror.

597
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,039
But I'm not letting you pay for this.

598
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:19,759
It's on me.

599
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,220
It's a long story.

600
00:21:22,470 --> 00:21:23,790
Let's get started.

601
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,790
The quarterly review session

602
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:27,640
is now underway.

603
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,030
Overall,

604
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,669
our division's performance metrics

605
00:21:30,670 --> 00:21:32,230
look quite promising.

606
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:33,710
However,

607
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:34,909
mediation rates are lagging.

608
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:36,319
Specifically regarding your cases.

609
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,559
This month,

610
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:38,879
I haven't seen a single one.

611
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:41,119
Every judge has different priorities.

612
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:42,559
My closure rate is the highest,

613
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:43,629
and my appeal rate is zero.

614
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:45,469
Both metrics are well above the average.

615
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:46,950
Your performance

616
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,149
speaks for itself.

617
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:49,519
No need to emphasize it.

618
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:50,709
We didn't call you here

619
00:21:50,710 --> 00:21:52,389
to reprimand you.

620
00:21:52,390 --> 00:21:54,229
We simply want

621
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:56,469
to discuss if there's any room

622
00:21:56,470 --> 00:21:58,080
for improvement on your end.

623
00:21:58,390 --> 00:21:59,519
In this regard,

624
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:01,989
Chief Judge Shu and Chief Judge Ying
have extensive experience.

625
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:02,909
So,

626
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:04,909
we're going to help you
analyze your cases.

627
00:22:04,910 --> 00:22:05,909
Please,

628
00:22:05,910 --> 00:22:07,710
try to keep an open mind.

629
00:22:07,950 --> 00:22:10,469
It's not about resisting you
or my seniors.

630
00:22:10,470 --> 00:22:11,629
It's that I fundamentally

631
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:13,470
disagree with the metric itself.

632
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,669
Mediation saves us from writing rulings

633
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:17,389
and the risk of an overturned verdict.

634
00:22:17,390 --> 00:22:18,669
To make life easier,

635
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:20,669
every judge would choose mediation.

636
00:22:20,670 --> 00:22:22,629
But when a judge acts
as a mere "peacemaker,"

637
00:22:22,630 --> 00:22:23,559
forcing the vulnerable

638
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,429
to compromise their principles

639
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:27,359
just to achieve
a superficial settlement

640
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,989
with both sides taking a step back,

641
00:22:28,990 --> 00:22:31,599
I find that disrespectful
to both parties.

642
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,229
It's a subversion of social ethics.

643
00:22:34,230 --> 00:22:37,200
Everything has two sides, Shen.

644
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,949
Upholding social ethics

645
00:22:38,950 --> 00:22:41,200
requires a broader perspective.

646
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,669
This is the Family Court.

647
00:22:42,670 --> 00:22:44,279
You can't treat these people

648
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:46,550
like they're in the Criminal Division,

649
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,359
(Execution Command Center)

650
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,989
The divorce case dragged
on for three years.

651
00:22:50,990 --> 00:22:53,429
The settlement has been
in effect for six months,

652
00:22:53,430 --> 00:22:55,669
yet my client has
only seen his child twice.

653
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,469
The grandmother has only seen him once.

654
00:22:57,470 --> 00:22:58,519
Two months ago,

655
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:02,519
the mother claimed the child
was emotionally unstable due to the divorce

656
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:03,949
and refused to meet my client.

657
00:23:03,950 --> 00:23:05,519
Now, two months later,

658
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,429
she's blaming pollen allergies.

659
00:23:07,430 --> 00:23:09,360
Pollen season is over.

660
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:12,519
So now she's nitpicking the location,

661
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:14,469
claiming it doesn't
match the settlement.

662
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:16,669
It's right there in black and white,

663
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:18,360
yet his rights are being ignored.

664
00:23:18,430 --> 00:23:20,160
Excuse me.

665
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:21,989
Ms. Qin, right?

666
00:23:21,990 --> 00:23:23,600
Pardon the interruption.

667
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:24,759
I'm a father myself,

668
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:26,119
so I truly understand

669
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:28,039
how much Mr. Zhou

670
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:29,799
misses his son.

671
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,319
And Article 1086 of the Civil Code

672
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,319
protects fathers like Mr. Zhou

673
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:35,669
in exercising their visitation rights.

674
00:23:35,670 --> 00:23:38,079
However, there are conditions
for those rights.

675
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:40,149
The child's well-being
must be guaranteed.

676
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:41,669
The records we have also show

677
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:42,879
that Mr. Zhou's job

678
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:44,879
is extremely demanding.

679
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:46,189
His interaction with the child

680
00:23:46,190 --> 00:23:47,629
has been very limited.

681
00:23:47,630 --> 00:23:49,189
Specifically, as they mentioned,

682
00:23:49,190 --> 00:23:50,519
during the years of litigation,

683
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,310
there were several intense conflicts

684
00:23:53,670 --> 00:23:55,389
between the families.

685
00:23:55,390 --> 00:23:56,599
At the time,

686
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,079
the boy was traumatized.

687
00:23:58,080 --> 00:23:59,799
So now, little Zhou Zhou

688
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,759
actually feels quite

689
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:03,909
fearful and resistant toward his father.

690
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:05,710
A meeting is not appropriate right now.

691
00:24:06,430 --> 00:24:07,319
Hold on a minute.

692
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,389
Were you there when we fought?

693
00:24:09,390 --> 00:24:10,359
Did you see it?

694
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,759
Did you see him get scared?

695
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:13,799
And the boy started resisting me then?

696
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,270
But not her?

697
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,149
When we were fighting,

698
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,750
she bit me here.

699
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:20,189
And she scratched me here.

700
00:24:20,190 --> 00:24:21,909
Why would my son fear me and not her?

701
00:24:21,910 --> 00:24:23,189
These are permanent scars.

702
00:24:23,190 --> 00:24:24,629
She's lucky I didn't sue her.

703
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,879
And saying I'm busy?

704
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:26,989
That I have no time for him?

705
00:24:26,990 --> 00:24:28,279
Is she not busy?

706
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:29,839
From the day my son was born

707
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:30,949
until he was two years old,

708
00:24:30,950 --> 00:24:32,079
she never cared for him.

709
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,510
His grandmother, my mother,
raised the boy.

710
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:36,359
I deserve some justice.

711
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,879
Fine, block me from seeing the kid,

712
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,229
but blocking my mother too?

713
00:24:39,230 --> 00:24:40,909
Of course the boy is a bit

714
00:24:40,910 --> 00:24:42,519
unfamiliar with us. It's only natural.

715
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:44,469
But she badmouths me to him every day.

716
00:24:44,470 --> 00:24:45,799
At this rate, the kid

717
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,400
won't even know I'm his father.

718
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,600
You really think a lot of yourself.

719
00:24:49,670 --> 00:24:51,429
I don't even bother
mentioning you to him.

720
00:24:51,430 --> 00:24:52,750
Ms. Lin.

721
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:55,160
Please put your phone away.

722
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:57,599
Thank you.

723
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,429
Even if you're right,

724
00:24:59,430 --> 00:25:01,279
is the happiness of the minority

725
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,759
not worth your effort?

726
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,429
No, but you have to consider

727
00:25:04,430 --> 00:25:06,189
the cost-effectiveness of litigation.

728
00:25:06,190 --> 00:25:07,119
A judgment

729
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:09,710
is just a formal way to end a dispute.

730
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:10,519
Mediation,

731
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:13,230
offers the parties
psychological closure.

732
00:25:13,390 --> 00:25:15,750
Why treat them as opposites?

733
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:18,319
Judging a case solely by numbers

734
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:19,790
isn't exactly objective.

735
00:25:19,990 --> 00:25:22,079
But with your talent,

736
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,559
and with so many cases,

737
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,360
can't you manage to mediate even one?

738
00:25:25,430 --> 00:25:28,669
I think you're just psychologically
opposed to it.

739
00:25:28,670 --> 00:25:31,080
Are you really that black and white?

740
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:33,559
Of course not.

741
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,669
But for a judge, I don't think

742
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:37,470
being binary is necessarily a bad thing.

743
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:40,559
Why are you so stubborn?

744
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:42,240
(Yao family)

745
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,030
The parties...

746
00:25:48,410 --> 00:25:49,090
Hello?

747
00:25:49,230 --> 00:25:50,389
Judge Shen.

748
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:52,119
My brother is doing better.

749
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,119
So,

750
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:54,879
when can you set a trial date?

751
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,629
He couldn't even speak yesterday.

752
00:25:56,630 --> 00:25:57,599
Suddenly he's fine today?

753
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,319
The doctor said he can be discharged.

754
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:01,230
The sooner the trial, the better.

755
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:03,909
I won't have them tiring my brother out

756
00:26:03,910 --> 00:26:05,270
for his money.

757
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,429
Give it a rest.

758
00:26:06,430 --> 00:26:08,389
Stop playing the devoted brother.

759
00:26:08,390 --> 00:26:09,469
Shut up!

760
00:26:09,470 --> 00:26:11,079
(Yao family)
You have no say in this.

761
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:12,559
He's my man. I care about him.

762
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:14,949
Your man? Give me a break.

763
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:17,599
The law doesn't recognize
that relationship.

764
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,629
- Where's your marriage certificate?
- Do you...

765
00:26:19,630 --> 00:26:21,799
Alright. That's enough fighting.

766
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,359
If you are certain

767
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:25,429
that the old man's health is stable

768
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:26,429
and he can handle it,

769
00:26:26,430 --> 00:26:27,949
(Judge Shen)
then I'll set a time for all of you

770
00:26:27,950 --> 00:26:29,160
to meet  in the Mediation Room...

771
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:29,990
Mediation?

772
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:31,799
We don't need mediation.

773
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,879
Just give us a ruling.

774
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,279
It won't take long.

775
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,470
Yeah, I agree. Just rule on it.

776
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:37,839
I can't do that.

777
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:39,359
My supervisors are right here,

778
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:40,389
and I just got a lecture.

779
00:26:40,390 --> 00:26:42,989
I'm supposed to prioritize mediation.

780
00:26:42,990 --> 00:26:45,519
I have to offer you gentle guidance.

781
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,669
Until we've done a few rounds,

782
00:26:46,670 --> 00:26:47,989
going to trial is forbidden.

783
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:49,359
That's ridiculous!

784
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:50,909
The old man is eighty years old.

785
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:52,519
How many days does he even have left?

786
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,080
What about the pension?

787
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:55,429
Who's going to get it?

788
00:26:55,430 --> 00:26:57,149
Me! Who else?

789
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:59,119
In your dreams! Why would you get it?

790
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:01,629
Why not? I'm his biological daughter!

791
00:27:01,630 --> 00:27:03,120
I haven't even finished!

792
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:04,909
Who do you think you are?

793
00:27:04,910 --> 00:27:07,039
I'll have the court clerk

794
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,629
send you the mediation schedule.

795
00:27:08,630 --> 00:27:10,429
I'm busy. I have to go.

796
00:27:10,430 --> 00:27:11,079
Wait, wait, wait!

797
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:12,510
- Wait!
- You can't...

798
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:15,360
Keep at it. Go ahead, keep fighting.

799
00:27:19,990 --> 00:27:20,839
Well, bosses...

800
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,310
Are you satisfied with

801
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:23,710
how I handled it?

802
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:27,680
I've read the mediation agreement.

803
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,559
The father could exercise

804
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:31,510
his visitation rights every Saturday.

805
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:31,909
Right?

806
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:34,469
At Penguin Fried Chicken
on Jinfang Road.

807
00:27:34,470 --> 00:27:35,669
Judge Wang, about that...

808
00:27:35,670 --> 00:27:38,189
The Penguin Fried Chicken
on Jinfang Road?

809
00:27:38,190 --> 00:27:40,599
That whole area started being
demolished last month.

810
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:41,949
It's been closed for a while now.

811
00:27:41,950 --> 00:27:42,909
Judge Wang.

812
00:27:42,910 --> 00:27:43,879
May I say something?

813
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:44,879
Go ahead.

814
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:45,429
Right.

815
00:27:45,430 --> 00:27:46,879
There are over a dozen

816
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,149
Penguin Fried Chicken outlets.

817
00:27:48,150 --> 00:27:50,149
There are three
just in the Qingcheng District.

818
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:52,559
Just because
one specific branch closed down,

819
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,599
my client is barred from seeing his son?

820
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,990
Isn't this just
a deliberate stall tactic?

821
00:27:57,470 --> 00:27:58,949
No one is trying to stall here.

822
00:27:58,950 --> 00:28:01,389
The Jinfang Road Penguin Fried Chicken

823
00:28:01,390 --> 00:28:03,949
was specified in the mediation agreement

824
00:28:03,950 --> 00:28:06,119
as the official spot for visitation.

825
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:07,149
We agreed on that location

826
00:28:07,150 --> 00:28:08,799
after a very thorough discussion.

827
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:10,119
And the main reason was that,

828
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,429
in the child's memory,

829
00:28:11,430 --> 00:28:13,360
that might be the only place

830
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:16,519
his father ever actually
took him out for a meal.

831
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:17,799
We were looking at it from his side.

832
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:19,519
We were trying to help Mr. Zhou out.

833
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:20,039
We thought

834
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:21,709
the boy might be less resistant there.

835
00:28:21,710 --> 00:28:22,909
By your logic,

836
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:25,229
my client should
petition the city to halt

837
00:28:25,230 --> 00:28:26,359
the redevelopment project.

838
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:28,600
Otherwise,
he'll never see his kid again.

839
00:28:28,630 --> 00:28:29,640
Well...

840
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,880
That's a bit extreme.

841
00:28:31,910 --> 00:28:32,949
That's not what I meant.

842
00:28:32,950 --> 00:28:35,879
If you're going
to fixate on the location

843
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,909
and insist on sticking to it,

844
00:28:37,910 --> 00:28:39,949
then I suggest you file a lawsuit.

845
00:28:39,950 --> 00:28:41,359
We can go through the courts

846
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:45,229
and have them designate
a new location for future visitation.

847
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:47,279
A suggestion?
I don't need your suggestions!

848
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:48,879
You're her lawyer. Stay in your lane.

849
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:50,189
You've got some nerve.

850
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:51,840
Calling us stubborn?

851
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:55,149
Does that kid really only remember
having one meal with me?

852
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:55,519
Come on.

853
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,750
Did his mother raise him
to have amnesia?

854
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,669
You're even suggesting another lawsuit?

855
00:28:59,670 --> 00:29:00,599
Our divorce litigation

856
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:02,270
has taken two whole years!

857
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,429
Another two years?

858
00:29:03,430 --> 00:29:04,709
Just to fight over a location?

859
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:05,279
Or whatever else?

860
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:06,759
By then, the kid won't even know me.

861
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:08,510
He'll be calling some stranger "Dad".

862
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:10,389
Mr. Zhou.

863
00:29:10,390 --> 00:29:11,559
Try to stay calm.

864
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:12,989
It's not that I'm not calm.

865
00:29:12,990 --> 00:29:14,680
Judge, look.

866
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:16,799
I just miss my son so much.

867
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:19,030
And his grandmother misses him too.

868
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:21,359
She's banging her head against the wall.

869
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:22,429
You have to help us.

870
00:29:22,430 --> 00:29:23,389
Please, do something.

871
00:29:23,390 --> 00:29:26,079
I brought both parties here to solve this,

872
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,279
not to escalate the conflict.

873
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:28,709
Right now,

874
00:29:28,710 --> 00:29:29,949
the heart of your dispute

875
00:29:29,950 --> 00:29:32,119
is simply the choice of location.

876
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:32,989
Correct?

877
00:29:32,990 --> 00:29:34,229
The branch on Jinfang Road

878
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,079
has been demolished.

879
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:36,550
It's gone for good.

880
00:29:36,710 --> 00:29:38,189
Filing a new lawsuit

881
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:39,149
just to pick a spot

882
00:29:39,150 --> 00:29:40,710
would be a waste of resources

883
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,360
and a drain on everyone involved.

884
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:45,319
Exactly. We don't want to
waste the court's time

885
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,669
or any other resources.

886
00:29:46,670 --> 00:29:47,389
So let's just...

887
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:49,160
Please, let me finish.

888
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,189
What I'm proposing is,

889
00:29:53,190 --> 00:29:54,839
would you both consider

890
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:56,600
moving the visitation location

891
00:29:56,710 --> 00:29:58,990
to our Enforcement Department?

892
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:01,119
I'm in!

893
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,149
- Absolutely.
- We're...

894
00:30:02,150 --> 00:30:03,680
I get to see my kid.

895
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:04,990
Ms. Lin?

896
00:30:05,190 --> 00:30:07,360
If we move the meeting point here...

897
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:12,710
I can't believe it.

898
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:15,319
That woman is such a piece of work.

899
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:15,949
She's so difficult,

900
00:30:15,950 --> 00:30:17,319
always whining and complaining.

901
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:18,189
And yet,

902
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:19,119
she actually agreed.

903
00:30:19,120 --> 00:30:21,279
I guess having friends
in high places pays off.

904
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:23,279
Pulling strings
with the judge worked wonders.

905
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:25,600
With the judge on our side,
that lawyer is nothing.

906
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:27,949
I don't mean you, Ms. Qin.

907
00:30:27,950 --> 00:30:29,599
I just meant...

908
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,319
Since the court offered up the place,

909
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:32,909
any smart lawyer on the other side

910
00:30:32,910 --> 00:30:34,400
wouldn't refuse.

911
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:36,799
This has nothing to do
with pulling strings.

912
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,990
Right. Sorry, slipped up there.

913
00:30:39,670 --> 00:30:41,189
But you really are the best.

914
00:30:41,190 --> 00:30:42,879
Humility is one of your many virtues.

915
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:44,229
Smart, hardworking,

916
00:30:44,230 --> 00:30:45,389
and sharp as a tack.

917
00:30:45,390 --> 00:30:47,790
You're brilliant, kind,
and always helpful.

918
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:49,799
Speaking of being helpful...

919
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,680
Could you help me with one more thing?

920
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,949
Put in another word with Judge Shen.

921
00:30:53,950 --> 00:30:56,160
Let's not meet here next time.

922
00:30:56,190 --> 00:30:58,669
Let's meet at my house so
the boy can see his grandmother, too.

923
00:30:58,670 --> 00:30:59,879
That won't work.

924
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,990
We already agreed
on the Enforcement Department.

925
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:03,989
If she has to,
just have your mother come along.

926
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:05,079
Wouldn't that work?

927
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:05,839
Right.

928
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,709
I haven't told you this yet, sorry...

929
00:31:08,710 --> 00:31:10,039
After the divorce,

930
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,189
my mother had an accident.

931
00:31:11,190 --> 00:31:12,640
She was injured.

932
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,559
It was serious.
She can't leave the house.

933
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:15,989
She hasn't seen my son in six months.

934
00:31:15,990 --> 00:31:17,429
She misses him every day.

935
00:31:17,430 --> 00:31:19,880
Forget the Department.
Let's do it at my house.

936
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,669
I know it's hard for her,

937
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:24,599
but now is definitely not the time.

938
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,949
Your ex-wife doesn't trust you.

939
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:28,030
We just finally got her to budge.

940
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:30,279
She's willing to meet at the Department.

941
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:32,230
Don't push your luck.

942
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:36,229
Look, here's what I think.

943
00:31:36,230 --> 00:31:38,039
Show up on time next week
to see the kid.

944
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:39,559
Leave a good impression on the judge.

945
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:40,759
Maybe the judge

946
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:42,319
will put in a good word for you later.

947
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:44,629
Then, I'll do my best
to make sure your mother

948
00:31:44,630 --> 00:31:46,120
gets to see the boy.

949
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,079
Forget about later.

950
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:50,279
It's just a quick favor for you, right?

951
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,709
Just let the old lady see him once.

952
00:31:51,710 --> 00:31:53,229
Give her a reason to keep going.

953
00:31:53,230 --> 00:31:55,039
If she can't walk, you can drive her.

954
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:56,279
Pick her up and bring her along.

955
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:57,559
Or use a wheelchair.

956
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:58,519
See him here.

957
00:31:58,520 --> 00:31:59,469
It's the same thing.

958
00:31:59,470 --> 00:32:00,629
How is that the same?

959
00:32:00,630 --> 00:32:01,599
It would be so simple

960
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:02,949
for the boy to visit her.

961
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:05,270
Why put the old lady
through all that trouble?

962
00:32:05,630 --> 00:32:07,839
Like I said, one step at a time.

963
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,469
Alright, don't get so worked up.

964
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:10,990
Go home and think about it.

965
00:32:12,910 --> 00:32:13,669
Fine.

966
00:32:13,670 --> 00:32:15,079
I'll leave a great impression

967
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:16,389
on dear Judge Shen.

968
00:32:16,390 --> 00:32:17,990
What do you mean?

969
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:20,510
It's Judge Wang!

970
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,550
Judge Wang, yes.

971
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:26,550
She's small,
but she's got quite a temper.

972
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:34,799
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

973
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:35,359
Hello, Mom.

974
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,200
So, how's it going? Are you off yet?

975
00:32:37,470 --> 00:32:38,790
Not yet.

976
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,709
I can hear the traffic.

977
00:32:40,710 --> 00:32:42,790
Were you just crossing the street?

978
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:45,310
I still have cases to handle
even when I'm home.

979
00:32:45,430 --> 00:32:47,149
I know you too well.

980
00:32:47,150 --> 00:32:48,519
With your productivity,

981
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,079
working at home is no different.

982
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:51,279
Besides,

983
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:54,270
you have a whole brain trust
waiting for you here.

984
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:03,440
But I suspect that brain trust is exactly
what you're avoiding.

985
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,310
We're missing some family members today.

986
00:33:10,630 --> 00:33:12,510
Come back and visit Grandpa.

987
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:17,229
The bosses lectured me today

988
00:33:17,230 --> 00:33:19,310
about my mediation rates.

989
00:33:19,470 --> 00:33:21,429
I need to spend the night figuring out

990
00:33:21,430 --> 00:33:22,759
how to be a mediator.

991
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,120
I really don't have time.

992
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:25,629
Fine.

993
00:33:25,630 --> 00:33:27,030
Suit yourself then.

994
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,560
(Son)

995
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:32,640
Is tricking him into coming back

996
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:35,310
really the sustainable way?

997
00:33:35,630 --> 00:33:37,559
If he actually came home today,

998
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:39,149
couldn't you, for Dad's sake,

999
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,759
just head out

1000
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:42,470
and grab a quick bite somewhere else?

1001
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,389
Now that you've exposed me,

1002
00:33:44,390 --> 00:33:45,559
this whole plan

1003
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:47,119
is definitely not sustainable.

1004
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:47,839
I don't think Dad

1005
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:50,400
wants family time built on lies.

1006
00:33:53,670 --> 00:33:54,629
Are you talking about me?

1007
00:33:54,630 --> 00:33:56,160
It's nothing. Go back to your game.

1008
00:33:57,320 --> 00:33:59,389
The bond between
mother, son, and grandson

1009
00:33:59,390 --> 00:34:01,839
is real, pure, and simple.

1010
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,400
(Son)
How is that a lie?

1011
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:06,710
The only problem is the relationship
between you and your son.

1012
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,319
With the temper your son has now,

1013
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,870
he won't bother to lie to you.

1014
00:34:10,720 --> 00:34:12,429
Don't you think you should
reflect on yourself?

1015
00:34:12,430 --> 00:34:14,160
Everything I do is for his own good.

1016
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:16,429
Why else would his bosses
grill him like that?

1017
00:34:16,430 --> 00:34:17,759
Do you think they're just bored

1018
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,200
and want to make his life tough?

1019
00:34:19,910 --> 00:34:21,469
I'm telling you, that son of yours

1020
00:34:21,470 --> 00:34:22,909
is too detached from the world.

1021
00:34:22,910 --> 00:34:24,159
He has no sense of human nature.

1022
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:24,799
Right.

1023
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:28,480
He's just a heartless
sentencing robot with no soul.

1024
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:31,720
(Mother)

1025
00:34:40,440 --> 00:34:44,799
(Jindian Law Firm)

1026
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:48,720
(Legal Consulting, Elite Lawyers.
Efficient & Professional.)

1027
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:56,440
(In a marriage, a wife who bears
the brunt of childcare and housework)

1028
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:02,400
(loses career opportunities.
Under the law, she can claim damages.)

1029
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:13,040
(Lian)

1030
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,390
Hey, Lian.

1031
00:35:17,430 --> 00:35:19,230
When are you coming home?

1032
00:35:19,470 --> 00:35:20,960
I'm on my way back now.

1033
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:22,279
What's for dinner?

1034
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,710
Let me see...

1035
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:27,469
In the fridge,

1036
00:35:27,470 --> 00:35:29,199
we've got a bunch of bok choy

1037
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,680
and half a celtuce.

1038
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:32,790
They'll go bad very soon.

1039
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:35,270
Garlic bok choy

1040
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:38,160
and celtuce with eggs. Perfect.

1041
00:35:38,200 --> 00:35:39,710
Celtuce with eggs?

1042
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,710
I wouldn't dare touch those eggs.

1043
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:44,159
Aren't those your "business assets"?

1044
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,239
You have to save them.

1045
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,509
The egg makes the chicken,
the chicken makes the egg.

1046
00:35:47,510 --> 00:35:50,790
It's a never-ending cycle of profit!

1047
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:53,589
Well, I just got my first payment.

1048
00:35:53,590 --> 00:35:54,909
Think of it as

1049
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:56,430
a special occasion.

1050
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:58,710
Really?

1051
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:00,159
In that case, hurry home.

1052
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:01,910
Time to feast!

1053
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:03,159
Alright.

1054
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:03,989
Wait for me.

1055
00:36:03,990 --> 00:36:05,109
One more spreadsheet,

1056
00:36:05,110 --> 00:36:06,389
and I'll be done.

1057
00:36:06,390 --> 00:36:08,160
Okay. See you in a bit.

1058
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:13,280
(You are entitled to half
of all marital assets upon divorce.)

1059
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,760
(Don't let them intimidate you.
Call for details.)

1060
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,000
Pardon me.

1061
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:28,000
You again?
Are you doing this on purpose?

1062
00:36:28,470 --> 00:36:30,520
Oh! Sorry about that, Judge Shen.

1063
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,080
I've got it.

1064
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:41,509
What are you looking for?

1065
00:36:41,510 --> 00:36:42,759
You don't think we have

1066
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:43,879
cameras in here, do you?

1067
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:45,589
In a tiny firm like ours,

1068
00:36:45,590 --> 00:36:47,029
we don't worry about thieves.

1069
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:48,230
Better that way.

1070
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:52,270
Judge Shen.

1071
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:55,430
This misunderstanding against me
seems to have gotten worse.

1072
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:57,109
About that side mirror...

1073
00:36:57,110 --> 00:36:58,759
My car has a dashcam too.

1074
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,600
360-degree coverage,
zero blind spots.

1075
00:37:02,110 --> 00:37:03,230
Fine.

1076
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:05,200
I admit it, I did it.

1077
00:37:05,430 --> 00:37:07,909
I was definitely
feeling a bit spiteful then.

1078
00:37:07,910 --> 00:37:08,989
Because I wouldn't help you

1079
00:37:08,990 --> 00:37:10,870
put on a show for your client?

1080
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,640
You mean Mr. Zhou?

1081
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:13,359
Look.

1082
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:14,989
That hotel encounter
was a total accident.

1083
00:37:14,990 --> 00:37:16,430
Pure coincidence.

1084
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:18,159
I don't know what's wrong with him,

1085
00:37:18,160 --> 00:37:20,199
but he has been convinced
that he needs "connections" to win.

1086
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:23,679
So you used me to make him think
you had a "backdoor" here.

1087
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:25,239
He came to that conclusion himself.

1088
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,759
That has nothing to do with me.

1089
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:27,719
If I say two words to you,

1090
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:29,960
he's probably already
picked out our baby's name.

1091
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,000
Besides,

1092
00:37:33,070 --> 00:37:35,520
what exactly do I gain
from his misunderstanding?

1093
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,359
Did I ask you for a favor?

1094
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,069
Did I give you money?
Did I even try to lobby you?

1095
00:37:39,070 --> 00:37:40,989
If you had, it would be bribing a judge.

1096
00:37:40,990 --> 00:37:42,910
Since you didn't, it's just fraud.

1097
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:44,279
Me, a fraud?

1098
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,879
You charged me
over three thousand for a mirror!

1099
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,279
Who's the real fraud here?

1100
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:49,639
I've already handed
the receipt to Ms. Liu.

1101
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:51,910
Take it up with the dealer
if you have a problem.

1102
00:37:52,550 --> 00:37:53,680
Unbelievable.

1103
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:57,040
My eggs!

1104
00:37:57,640 --> 00:37:58,790
From now on,

1105
00:37:59,070 --> 00:38:01,509
anytime, anywhere,

1106
00:38:01,510 --> 00:38:04,239
please maintain a distance
of at least two meters.

1107
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,069
I have no interest in causing

1108
00:38:06,070 --> 00:38:08,160
any more unnecessary misunderstandings.

1109
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:10,279
Two meters?

1110
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:10,909
Correct.

1111
00:38:10,910 --> 00:38:12,920
Regardless of whether clients are around?
Even outside the court?

1112
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:13,750
Yes.

1113
00:38:13,910 --> 00:38:15,069
One meter...

1114
00:38:15,070 --> 00:38:16,719
Two meters? From here?

1115
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:17,680
Exactly.

1116
00:38:17,910 --> 00:38:19,319
These are public roads!

1117
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:20,469
I'll stand wherever I please.

1118
00:38:20,470 --> 00:38:21,549
What's it to you?

1119
00:38:21,550 --> 00:38:23,509
You can call the shots at your court,

1120
00:38:23,510 --> 00:38:25,359
but this is Jindian Law Firm.

1121
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:27,390
If anyone's setting rules here, it's me.

1122
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:29,549
Not leaving?

1123
00:38:29,550 --> 00:38:30,109
Fine.

1124
00:38:30,110 --> 00:38:31,069
Let me show you

1125
00:38:31,070 --> 00:38:33,200
what a two-meter gap looks like.

1126
00:38:36,390 --> 00:38:37,589
This is two meters.

1127
00:38:37,590 --> 00:38:39,719
From now on,
whenever you pass our firm,

1128
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:40,799
take the long way around.

1129
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:42,429
If you set foot on our property,

1130
00:38:42,430 --> 00:38:44,679
even by a fraction of an inch,
we'll have a problem.

1131
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:47,350
Are you serious?
Did you pave this road yourself?

1132
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:48,389
You're over the line.

1133
00:38:48,390 --> 00:38:50,109
Since when did your storefront
extend this far?

1134
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:51,069
It's as far as I say it is.

1135
00:38:51,070 --> 00:38:52,199
I'm the silent guardian.

1136
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:54,239
I sweep these streets
all the way to your court.

1137
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,270
This whole area is my territory.

1138
00:38:56,390 --> 00:38:57,549
You're impossible.

1139
00:38:57,550 --> 00:38:59,279
(Jindian Law Firm)

1140
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,589
Don't run away, Judge Shen!

1141
00:39:00,590 --> 00:39:01,870
I'm getting this on video!

1142
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:04,799
Look, it's Judge Shen Xiezhi
of Qingcheng Court.

1143
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,389
Stop right there! I dare you to stay!

1144
00:39:06,390 --> 00:39:08,159
Look at him, lurking around our firm.

1145
00:39:08,160 --> 00:39:09,199
What's his agenda?

1146
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,549
What dark secrets is he hiding?

1147
00:39:10,550 --> 00:39:12,520
Stay tuned as we find out!

1148
00:39:12,590 --> 00:39:15,040
I hope your bosses launch
a full investigation.

1149
00:39:15,390 --> 00:39:17,200
You're absolutely ridiculous.

1150
00:39:17,360 --> 00:39:18,910
Now I've gotten under his skin!

1151
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:22,389
Driving him off is a blessing
for the legal system.

1152
00:39:22,390 --> 00:39:24,480
You're out of your league.

1153
00:39:27,390 --> 00:39:29,350
Wait, I'm already off the clock.

1154
00:39:30,430 --> 00:39:32,310
The court's motor pool
has been tight lately.

1155
00:39:32,550 --> 00:39:33,589
Last time you went out,

1156
00:39:33,590 --> 00:39:35,200
you used your personal car again.

1157
00:39:35,510 --> 00:39:36,949
Not enough cars for the judges.

1158
00:39:36,950 --> 00:39:38,069
The paperwork is cumbersome.

1159
00:39:38,070 --> 00:39:39,520
It's easier just to drive my own.

1160
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:43,279
With three trials
and a field visit today,

1161
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,759
the gas subsidy won't even cover it.

1162
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:45,960
File the claim later.

1163
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:49,230
It's just cheap gas. I'm being frugal.

1164
00:39:49,430 --> 00:39:50,910
File for reimbursement.

1165
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:53,270
Understood. Thank you, Judge Shen.

1166
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:00,759
Where's the tissue?

1167
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:01,960
Right here.

1168
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:13,710
Sorry about the mess.
There's a fresh pack below.

1169
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,230
Good grief.

1170
00:40:18,470 --> 00:40:20,230
You're incredibly meticulous.

1171
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,549
My memory's shot,
so I write things down.

1172
00:40:22,550 --> 00:40:24,870
Why keep them
if you've already finished the task?

1173
00:40:25,240 --> 00:40:27,000
To review them whenever I can.

1174
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,870
If I actually had a good memory,

1175
00:40:28,910 --> 00:40:31,040
I wouldn't have failed
the bar exam seven times.

1176
00:40:37,030 --> 00:40:38,750
Have a seat. I'll be right with you.

1177
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:55,239
Didn't I take that out?

1178
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:56,870
Why did you put it back in?

1179
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:58,359
Zhou Zhou's mom doesn't
let him have candy.

1180
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,839
She'll blow up at you again.

1181
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:00,910
Put it away.

1182
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:03,679
Just put it away. Do as I say.

1183
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,319
Just hide it.

1184
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:07,080
His mother is such a nitpicker.

1185
00:41:11,590 --> 00:41:13,359
Once she gets here,
she'll cause a scene.

1186
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:14,029
Just you watch.

1187
00:41:14,030 --> 00:41:16,080
You won't be seeing
your grandson anytime soon.

1188
00:41:18,510 --> 00:41:19,909
Just wait right here.

1189
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:21,469
I'll definitely
bring him back to see you.

1190
00:41:21,470 --> 00:41:22,480
Okay?

1191
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:28,600
I'll take a look.

1192
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:49,029
Ms. Qin.

1193
00:41:49,030 --> 00:41:50,310
Mr. Zhou.

1194
00:41:51,910 --> 00:41:52,989
I brought my mother with me.

1195
00:41:52,990 --> 00:41:54,750
She's sitting by the entrance for now.

1196
00:41:56,070 --> 00:41:58,120
Why didn't you let her come in?

1197
00:41:58,550 --> 00:42:00,350
When she heard
about seeing her grandson,

1198
00:42:00,590 --> 00:42:01,319
she got excited.

1199
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:03,389
She hasn't
left the house in over a year.

1200
00:42:03,390 --> 00:42:04,759
If Lin Yanping says something nasty,

1201
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:05,719
it's going to break

1202
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:06,679
my mother's heart.

1203
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:08,200
I don't want her to suffer.

1204
00:42:08,910 --> 00:42:09,639
I understand.

1205
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:10,799
Once the boy arrives,

1206
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:12,160
I'll invite her inside.

1207
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:16,469
Judge Wang.

1208
00:42:16,470 --> 00:42:17,549
Welcome.

1209
00:42:17,550 --> 00:42:18,469
The other side arrived.

1210
00:42:18,470 --> 00:42:19,839
They're looking for a parking spot.

1211
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,949
It'll take a few minutes.

1212
00:42:20,950 --> 00:42:23,199
I'll call you when they're in.
Just hang on a bit longer.

1213
00:42:23,200 --> 00:42:24,279
What do you mean?

1214
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,239
Looking for a parking spot?

1215
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,029
When I pulled into the lot,

1216
00:42:27,030 --> 00:42:28,159
there were spots everywhere!

1217
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:29,469
She's doing this on purpose.

1218
00:42:29,470 --> 00:42:31,029
She's keeping the court waiting

1219
00:42:31,030 --> 00:42:31,679
to be difficult.

1220
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:33,359
Isn't this
contempt of court or something?

1221
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:33,759
That's enough.

1222
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:36,200
I know exactly what qualifies
as contempt, Mr. Zhou.

1223
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:37,600
Mr. Zhou,

1224
00:42:37,950 --> 00:42:39,719
let me give you some personal advice.

1225
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:40,879
Fix that temper of yours.

1226
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,199
You've got a short fuse.

1227
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,949
If you trigger the child's resentment,

1228
00:42:43,950 --> 00:42:45,759
even we won't be able to help you.

1229
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:46,799
Right, of course.

1230
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:47,839
Thank you, Judge Wang.

1231
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,799
I'll make sure my client keeps his cool.

1232
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,160
Thanks for the heads-up.

1233
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:55,159
My temper?

1234
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:57,350
What's wrong with my temper?

1235
00:42:57,950 --> 00:42:59,719
What kind of attitude was that?

1236
00:42:59,720 --> 00:43:00,159
Trust me,

1237
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,799
he's in cahoots with Lin Yanping.

1238
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,069
I wouldn't be surprised

1239
00:43:03,070 --> 00:43:04,310
if she got to him somehow.

1240
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1241
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1242
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1243
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1244
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1245
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1246
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1247
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1248
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1249
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1250
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1251
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1252
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1253
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1254
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1255
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1256
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1257
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1258
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1259
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1260
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1261
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1262
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1263
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1264
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1265
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1266
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1267
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1268
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1269
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1270
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1271
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1272
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1273
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1274
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1275
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
